title: Watch live: SpaceX on track for predawn launch from Cape Canaveral
summary: Another batch of 56 Starlink satellites will rocket into orbit from Cape Canaveral before dawn Thursday aboard a Falcon 9 launcher, continuing the deployment of SpaceX’s second-generation internet constellation begun last month. Liftoff is scheduled for 4:22 a.m. EST (0922 GMT).

title: Lamborn named chair of House Armed Services strategic forces subcommittee
summary: Rep. Doug Lamborn, a Republican representing Colorado Springs, was named chairman of the House Armed Services Committee’s strategic forces subcommittee.

title: NASA Awards Innovations, Partnership Support Services Agreements
summary: NASA has selected six companies to provide early-stage innovations and partnership support services. The services will be provided across multiple NASA centers. The place of performance will be specified in each specific call, with much of the work being performed virtually.

title: SpaceX launches Starlink Group 5-2 mission from Florida
summary: SpaceX’s busy 2023 continued with the launch of Starlink 5-2, a mission that plans to fill out new “shells” of Starlink satellites that link to the upcoming second-generation Starlink constellation. The Starlink 5-2 mission launched into the predawn darkness at 4:32 AM EST (09:32 UTC) on Thursday, Jan. 26, from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.

title: ESA is no longer planning to send astronauts to China’s Tiangong space station
summary: ESA’s Director General says the agency does not have the budgetary capacity nor the political intention to send its astronauts to China’s space station.

title: NASA will join a military program to develop nuclear thermal propulsion
summary: None of this will happen quickly. The technology is difficult and unproven.

title: Rocket Lab establishes new U.S. foothold with successful launch after years of delays
summary: Rocket Lab’s first U.S. launch got off the ground Tuesday evening, marking a successful mission and a long-awaited expansion of the company’s capabilities.

title: Spaceflight books dedicated Isar Aerospace launch in 2026
summary: U.S.-based launch services provider Spaceflight said Jan. 25 it has booked a dedicated launch in 2026 from Isar Aerospace, the German rocket developer aiming to perform the first test flight of its Spectrum vehicle this year.

title: Astrobotic completes Peregrine testing
summary: Astrobotic Technologies said that it has completed testing of its Peregrine lunar lander and it ready to ship it to Cape Canaveral for launch.
